relevant_findings.general: Obese woman in no acute distress (NAD), comfortable, appropriate, sleepy but arousable to questioning.
relevant_findings.heent: Normocephalic/atraumatic, pupils equal, round, reactive to light and accommodation (PERRLA), extraocular movements intact (EOMI), sclerae anicteric, moist mucous membranes (MMM), oropharynx clear.
relevant_findings.neck: Supple, no thyromegaly, no jugular venous distention (JVD), no carotid bruits.
relevant_findings.heart: Regular rate and rhythm (RRR), no murmurs, rubs or gallops (MRG), normal S1-S2.
relevant_findings.lungs: Clear to auscultation bilaterally (CTA), no rales, rhonchi or wheezes, good air movement, respirations unlabored.
relevant_findings.abdomen: Obese, mild epigastric tenderness to palpation, no rebound or guarding, normal bowel sounds, do not appreciate organomegaly but examination limited by obesity.
relevant_findings.neurological: Awake, alert and oriented x3, cranial nerves II-XII grossly intact, fluent speech.

physical_examinations.changes_over_time: Nausea and diffuse abdominal pain improved after treatment.
